1.what is the three way TCP handshake?
 A TCP 3-way handshake is a foundational networking process used to establish a reliable,connection oriented session between a client and a server.
 It utilizes three distinct messages(SYN,SYN-ACK and ACK) to ensure both devices are synchronized and ready to exchange data securly.
2.When would you use TCP over UDP?
  TCP is used over UDP whenever reliability ,dataintegrity,correct sequencing are more important than raw speed.Because TCP establishes a connection 
  and guarantees that every single packet arrives safely and in the correct order,it is the backbone of applications where losing even a tiny bit of
  data could corrupt the entire file or message.
3.When would you use UDP over TCP?
  UDP is used over TCP when speed,low latency and real -time delivery are more important than perfect accuracy.Because UDP is a "fire-and-forget"
  protocol,it does not waste time establishing a connection ,checking if data arrived or re-sending lost packets.
